10 SUMMARY
1111 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, clarifies that the
1122 apartments created by the Island Nursing Home must be rented to individuals 55 years of
1133 age or older whose household income is no more than 80% of the median income for the
1144 area as defined by the United States Department of Housing and Urban Development. It
1155 also extends the Maine State Housing Authority's reporting deadline by 6 months.
